#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.f:2
msgid "Draw samples from an F distribution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.f:4
msgid ""
"Samples are drawn from an F distribution with specified parameters, `dfnum` "
"(degrees of freedom in numerator) and `dfden` (degrees of freedom in "
"denominator), where both parameters must be greater than zero."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.f:9
msgid ""
"The random variate of the F distribution (also known as the Fisher "
"distribution) is a continuous probability distribution that arises in ANOVA "
"tests, and is the ratio of two chi-square variates."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.f:0
msgid "Parameters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.f:17
msgid "**dfnum**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.f:-1
msgid "float or array_like of floats"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.f:17
msgid "Degrees of freedom in numerator, must be > 0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.f:20
msgid "**dfden**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.f:-1
msgid "float or array_like of float"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.f:20
msgid "Degrees of freedom in denominator, must be > 0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.f:28
msgid "**size**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.f:-1
msgid "int or tuple of ints, optional"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.f:23
msgid ""
"Output shape.  If the given shape is, e.g., ``(m, n, k)``, then ``m * n * "
"k`` samples are drawn.  If size is ``None`` (default), a single value is "
"returned if ``dfnum`` and ``dfden`` are both scalars. Otherwise, ``np."
"broadcast(dfnum, dfden).size`` samples are drawn."
msgstr ""

