msgid "ndarray or scalar"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.f:33
msgid "Drawn samples from the parameterized Fisher distribution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.f:44
msgid ":obj:`scipy.stats.f`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.f:45
msgid ""
"probability density function, distribution or cumulative density function, "
"etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.f:49
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.f:50
msgid ""
"The F statistic is used to compare in-group variances to between-group "
"variances. Calculating the distribution depends on the sampling, and so it "
"is a function of the respective degrees of freedom in the problem.  The "
"variable `dfnum` is the number of samples minus one, the between-groups "
"degrees of freedom, while `dfden` is the within-groups degrees of freedom, "
"the sum of the number of samples in each group minus the number of groups."
msgstr ""

